<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-07-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-07-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="290" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/764.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">The
                                        Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-07-19"><hi rend="italic">July 19,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Beaupré acknowledges department’s cablegram of July 14, and says that
                            September 15 will be satisfactory to the Government of the Netherlands
                            for meeting of opium conference. Mr. Beaupré adds that the minister for
                            foreign affairs desires to be informed at once what Governments have
                            adhered to the principle of the calling of the conference so that
                            invitations may be issued.</p>
                    </div>
